cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.SY

The paper discusses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and proposes a new dataflow and multi-mode inference engine for efficient computation of CNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also discusses hardware solutions and power consumption, which could fall under cs.ET (Embedded Systems) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the proposed dataflow and inference engine could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-categories.
